"text":". (M, Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trd~Y bisayofihi","text_ar":"تردّى بِسَيْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtdY","text_ar":"ارتدى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hung upon himself his sword, putting its suspensory belt or cord upon his neck or shoulder;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqal~adahu","text_ar":"تَقَلَّدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trd~t AljaAriyapu","text_ar":"تردّت الجَارِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The girl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young woman, put on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decked herself with, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wi$aAH","text_ar":"وِشَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], which is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ridaA='","text_ar":"رِدَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%89/","headword_ar":"تردّى","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_39","lexicon_en":"ʿAbdullāh ibn ʿAbbās, Gharīb al-Qurʾān fī Shiʿr al-ʿArab, also known as Masāʾil Nāfiʿ b. al-Azraq (d. 687 CE)","lexicon_ar":"غريب القرآن في شعر العرب لعبد الله بن عباس","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=94273#3ae66c","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">ر د ى [تردّى]</span><br><span>قال: يا ابن عباس: أخبرني عن قول الله عزّ وجلّ: إِذا تَرَدَّى .</span><br><span>قال: إذا مات وتردّى في النار، قال: نزلت في أبي جهل .</span><br><span>قال: وهل تعرف العرب ذلك؟</span><br><span>قال: نعم، أما سمعت عدي بن زيد وهو يقول:</span><br><span>خطفته منية فتردّى </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> وهو في الملك يأمل التعميرا </span>"}]}}